--- body ---
## Context

Triage outcome of the 2026-07-22 dedup error-rate diagnosis (session
f373ecb2; estimates in 0301): three dedup defects are real but must NOT be
fixed on corpus v1 — any change to catalog_merge's dedup logic alters
unified_works and cascades into every archived artifact the R&R papers cite.
They are quantified and *reported in the text* now (0276/0277 prose), and
*fixed* in the corpus v2 rebuild (0288 lineage), where a full re-run is
planned anyway.

## Actions

1. **DOI-collision guard** (FP, ~40 groups, ~5% of DOI removals): in the DOI
   pass, refuse to merge same-DOI records whose normalized-title overlap is
   near zero (threshold from config); keep both and flag for review. These
   are OpenAlex DOI collisions between unrelated works.
2. **Non-empty-year key** (FP, ~5-10 wrong merges): the title+year pass
   currently merges records with EMPTY year across all unknown years
   ("climate finance|" collapsed 6 distinct no-DOI works). Require a
   non-empty year for the composite key, or add a same-author condition for
   empty-year groups.
3. **Author-aware WP/published matching** (FN, referee R1-12 suggestion):
   third pass — exact-or-fuzzy title + normalized author lastname + year gap
   <= 5 merges preprint/WP with the published version (~315 pairs, ~0.5% of
   v1 corpus). Requires author-name normalization first: v1 metadata swaps
   given/family names between sources (0301's C-finding). Decide and document
   the canonical-version policy (keep published, redirect citations).
4. Re-run the byte-compare discipline against v1 to enumerate exactly which
   records each change adds/removes; archive the delta as a run report.

## Test

- Fixture triple: a DOI collision (same DOI, unrelated titles) stays split;
  an empty-year generic-title pair stays split; a WP/published pair with
  swapped author-name order merges.

## Verification

- [ ] Per-change delta counts in a run report, reconciling with 0301's
      estimates (~40 / ~10 / ~315)

## Invariants

- v1 artifacts untouched — this lands only in the v2 lineage (0288).

## Exit criteria

- [ ] Three hardening changes implemented behind the v2 build
- [ ] Delta vs v1 archived and cited in the data paper's revision notes
